column5: I had a last minute cancellation this morning, so Cal and I took advantage of it and headed to a new zone to try it out.  Punched a few holes and set up a couple huts, even got his brother out for a while. Fishing was tough, not sure if it was a rough zone or the bite wasnt on today. Cal managed a couple fish, I lost my only one on the way up because I stopped reeling to grab the camera.  Ah well, its the way she goes... Tomorrows looking too cold for my blood, but I'll be back atter shortly...  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4a4_qbQyqUY
Great vid Steve.Were heading out in the cold.Have heater,will travel,,,,,,,,,,not to far,but will travel.LOL  Thanks for sharing
Great video Steve Seems like you guys have them whities and lakers dialed in Thanks for sharing Leechman
I was out for lakers today up near Sault Ste. Marie and the cold air/clear skies hit here around 2 and we were back at the camp by 3.  This on what was already a cold day!  sweet vid buddy.
They're saying -38 with windchill in Barrie, glad I'm not out there today
